<li id="c66">
  <div class="cx" id="cx51132775">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">How to judge a charity</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1216963/51132775#c66?mode=alone;showrate=1#c66">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>There has been a lot of discussion about the value of charities and it's pretty much a consensus that you DO NOT judge a charity on its low overhead. Using the example of the Make A Wish Foundation, they made $20 million for the cause.</p>
<p>Would it have been better if they made a measly ten grand but had a small 3% overhead?</p>
<p>What am I missing? What is this list missing?</p>

